name: Jimmer Fredette
summary: Jimmer Fredette, the former BYU star and college basketball sensation, is making a comeback at the 2024 Paris Olympics. He will represent Team USA in the 3x3 basketball competition, which is being introduced for the first time at the Olympics. Despite a disappointing debut loss to Serbia, Team USA and Fredette remain optimistic about their chances of winning the gold medal. Fredette's inclusion in the 3x3 squad highlights his resilience and continued pursuit of basketball glory. This opportunity provides him with a chance to redeem himself after a brief and unsuccessful stint in the NBA and showcase his exceptional skills on a global stage.

name: Paul Blackburn
summary: The New York Mets have acquired starting pitcher Paul Blackburn from the Oakland Athletics in a trade. Blackburn, a former All-Star, will join the Mets' rotation and provide depth to their starting staff. The Mets also added two relievers, Eudor Garcia and Joel Payamps, to bolster their bullpen. In exchange, the Mets sent pitching prospect Kade Morris to the Athletics. Blackburn has a 7-5 record with a 3.43 ERA in 18 starts this season. He has been a consistent performer for the Athletics, posting a 3.91 ERA in 71 career starts. The Mets are hoping that Blackburn can continue his success in New York and help them compete for a playoff spot.

name: Tanner Scott
summary: The San Diego Padres have made a significant trade to bolster their bullpen, acquiring All-Star closer Tanner Scott and starter Martín Pérez from the Miami Marlins. In exchange, the Padres sent four prospects to the Marlins. Scott, a 26-year-old right-hander, has been one of the most dominant relievers in baseball this season, with a 1.51 ERA and 10.4 strikeouts per nine innings. Pérez, a 31-year-old left-hander, has a 4.58 ERA in 2022 but has been a consistent starter throughout his career. The Padres are making a push for the playoffs and view Scott and Pérez as key additions to their roster. The Marlins, on the other hand, are rebuilding and are looking to add young talent to their organization.
